item.title: Red - Innocence & Instinct
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
Innocence & Instinct is the second full-length concept album from American Christian metal band Red. The album was released on February 10, 2009 through Essential Records.
The standard edition of the album contains 10 tracks. The first single "Fight Inside" was released on October 26, 2008. The single debuted at No. 1 on the R&R Christian Rock chart. The album's second single, "Never Be the Same", was released to Christian CHR soon thereafter. On December 12, the third single from the album, "Death of Me", was released to Active, Mainstream, and Alternative Rock stations. The album was produced by Rob Graves. The band also released a deluxe edition which features four bonus tracks and a DVD. Some copies of Innocence & Instinct contain the song "Forever" as track nine instead of "Out From Under". The track "Shadows" was co-written by Breaking Benjamin guitarist/vocalist Ben Burnley. The album debuted at No. 15 on the Billboard 200, selling 39,000 copies in its first week.
The Deluxe Edition of Innocence & Instinct went as high as No. 2 on iTunes Top Selling Rock Albums Chart and No. 5 on Top-Selling Albums overall, gaining a cumulative five-star review from listeners.[citation needed]
For the album, an ARG[jargon] was orchestrated by the band members. Red fans went through hidden web pages and passwords until around the time the album itself was released, when the final page was revealed, which contained a video message from the band itself, nine "treasures" (including posters, videos, and an unreleased track), and a message telling the puzzle participants not to post the contents on the internet or share them.[citation needed]
Drums on the album were played by Joe Rickard, the band's touring drummer. Rickard was not an official member of Red when the album was released, but has since been added as a permanent member.
In an interview on The Daily Rock, Jasen Rauch talks about the band not wanting "Ordinary World" added to the album. He states that Red originally arranged it just for something to do live. He goes on to say that the label pushed for it to be added to the album.
The album was nominated for Best Rock or Rap Gospel Album in the 2010 Grammy Awards. It won for Best Rock Album at the 41st GMA Dove Awards in 2010.
As of 2011, the album has sold over 260,000 copies.
item.excerpt:encoded: Innocence & Instinct is the second full-length concept album from American Christian metal band Red. The album was released on February 10, 2009 through Essential Records.

item.title: Pearl Jam - Ten
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
Ten is the debut studio album by the American grunge band Pearl Jam, released on August 27, 1991 through Epic Records. Following the disbanding of bassist Jeff Ament and guitarist Stone Gossard's previous group Mother Love Bone, the two recruited vocalist Eddie Vedder, guitarist Mike McCready, and drummer Dave Krusen to form Pearl Jam in 1990. Most of the songs began as instrumental jams, to which Vedder added lyrics about topics such as depression, homelessness, and abuse.
Ten was not an immediate success, but by late 1992 it had reached number two on the Billboard 200 chart. The album produced three hit singles: "Alive", "Even Flow", and "Jeremy". While Pearl Jam was accused of jumping on the grunge bandwagon at the time, Ten was instrumental in popularizing alternative rock in the mainstream. The album has been certified diamond by the RIAA in the United States. By June 2011, it had sold 9,869,000 copies, and remains Pearl Jam's most commercially successful album.
item.excerpt:encoded: Ten is the debut studio album by the American grunge band Pearl Jam, released on August 27, 1991 through Epic Records.

item.title: Gungor - Beautiful Things
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
Michael Gungor studied jazz at both Western Michigan University and the University of North Texas, while working as a worship leader in local churches.
After moving to Colorado, the group's name changed from "The Michael Gungor Band" to simply "Gungor". The first album to be released after the name change was "Beautiful Things" in 2010. In 2011, the song and the album "Beautiful Things" were nominated for the Grammy categories Best Gospel Song and Best Rock or Rap Gospel Album, respectively.

item.title: The Civil Wars - Barton Hollow
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
Barton Hollow is the first full-length studio album from independent group The Civil Wars. Helmed by Grammy Award-winning producer Charlie Peacock, it was released on February 1, 2011, and became the #1 downloaded album on iTunes that same week. It also charted at #1 on the Billboard Digital Albums chart, #12 on the US Billboard 200, #2 on the Billboard Folk Albums chart, and #3 on the Billboard Rock Albums chart.
The album was preceded by the lead single title track, which was performed live on The Tonight Show with Jay Leno on January 14. As of the chart dated June 4, 2011, the album has sold 94,781 copies in the US.

item.title: iPod Touch
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
The world's most popular portable gaming device is even more fun. Now available in black and white, iPod touch includes iOS 5 with over 200 new features, like iMessage, Notification Center, and Twitter integration. Send free, unlimited text messages over Wi-Fi with iMessage. Record HD video and make FaceTime calls. Visit the App Store to choose from over 500,000 apps. iPod touch also features iCloud, which stores your music, photos, apps, and more and wirelessly pushes them to all your devices.
New Features iMessage Now you can be all you want. Send unlimited text messages to any iOS 5 device free over Wi-Fi with iMessage.
Notification Center You're about to beat the final boss. Now's not the time for an alert to get in the way. And it won't, thanks to Notification Center.
Game Center Get ready to rumble. Game Center lets you play against friends and people you don't know. And it recommends new games and new opponents.
Twitter Integration Twitter users rejoice. iOS 5 adds Twitter capabilities to Safari, Photos, Camera, YouTube, and Maps, so you can tweet directly from them.
Reminders Forget much? Reminders can fix that for you. Create lists of things to do or remember, set a deadline, and Reminders sends you an alert.
Safari Web articles minus the ads. What bliss. Tap the Reader button in Safari and ads disappear. Add article links to Reading List and read them later.
Photos Photo Stream in iCloud stores all your latest photos and pushes them wirelessly to your other devices. So every pic is everywhere.
PC Free You can activate and set up your iPod touch wirelessly, right out of the box. Without the need for a Mac or PC.
Newsstand A magazine rack that's just for you. That's the idea behind Newsstand. Find all your publications here and even subscribe to new ones.
item.excerpt:encoded: The world's most popular portable gaming device is even more fun. Now available in black and white, iPod touch includes iOS 5 with over 200 new features.

item.title: MacBook Air
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded: Designing MacBook Air came with one goal: Create an incredibly thin and light notebook computer that’s every bit as powerful and capable as one twice its size. With flash storage, durable unibody construction, Multi-Touch technology, and a long-lasting battery, MacBook Air not only achieves that goal, it sets a new standard for what every notebook should be. Perfected down to the millimeter.
item.excerpt:encoded: Designing MacBook Air came with one goal: Create an incredibly thin and light notebook computer that’s every bit as powerful and capable as one twice its size.

item.title: iPod Nano
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded: The best things in life have a soundtrack, and that’s where iPod nano shines. The easy-to-use Multi-Touch display gives you total control of your music experience. Tap to play, or tap Music to browse your collection by songs, albums, artists, playlists, genres, or composers. You can even customize your Home screens so your music is organized just how you like.
item.excerpt:encoded: The best things in life have a soundtrack, and that’s where iPod nano shines.

item.title: AC Slater
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
Fact: A.C. Slater Almost Wrestled At Iowa.
Fancy yourself a "Saved by the Bell" fan? Or maybe you need something to show off your "I Heart A.C. Slater" tattoo? The only other reason you'd buy this shirt is if you love Iowa wrestling with all your heart and soul. Be a real fan. Buy this shirt.

item.title: Wooden Pirate Ship
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
This pirate ship pull toy was lovingly handmade out of poplar from start to finish, hand sanded smooth, painted with a wash of AP certified non-toxic watercolors and finished with natural beeswax creme to seal the wood. Details are wood burned so they'll never wear away. Edges are hand sanded to make them smooth and slightly rounded - perfect for little hands! The pull cord is natural cotton.
The pirate ship pull toy measures 7 inches long by 7 inches tall by 2 inches wide. The wheels are 1 3/4 inches wide. The pull cord is 24 inches long. Our four year old was able to pull it comfortably.
item.excerpt:encoded: This pirate ship pull toy was lovingly handmade out of poplar from start to finish.

item.title: Rustic Antique Blocks
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
The "Rustic Whimsical" set is a fun, unique looking set that's gender neutral. This set of 6 classic wooden blocks comes with each letter of the alphabet, some fun designs and extra letters to make spelling word a little easier.
Kids of all ages enjoy these blocks, they can stack and knock down, build a castle, pretend they're cars...oh, the possibilities are endless!
Each block is 1.75 inches square. These are made of natural cedar wood - Hand cut and sanded. They are large enough so they’re not a choking hazard, small enough so they’re easy for little hands to grasp.
Edges are hand-sanded for a soft, well worn edge. I also added a non-toxic sepia/antique copper tone to the edges to give it the authentic, worn and vintage look. Images are coated with a non-toxic sealer and are water resistant.
item.excerpt:encoded: The "Rustic Whimsical" set is a fun, unique looking set that's gender neutral. This set of 6 classic wooden blocks comes with each letter of the alphabet, some fun designs and extra letters to make spelling word a little easier.

item.title: Wooden Toy Truck
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
All natural wooden toys make smiling little girls and boys...
Let the good times roll with our organic wooden flat bed toy truck! Your little munchkin will have tons of fun loading, driving, and unloading -- also includes a removable driver. Locally grown black walnut wood makes this truck eco-friendly and STYLING!
item.excerpt:encoded: Let the good times roll with our organic wooden flat bed toy truck! Your little munchkin will have tons of fun loading, driving, and unloading -- also includes a removable driver.

item.title: Organic Toy Car
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded:
Cruise in style! One organic wooden toy car - our SUNDAY CRUISER - for your little one. You choose the color! This hip rider is organically finished, smooth as your little one's bum, and ready for miles of adventure. All natural nursery decor, this little treasure is delightfully simple, safe, and fun!
Measures: 5" x 3.5". Lovingly handmade in our family woodshop. Finished with our very own blend of organic camelina oil (a relative of flaxseed) and beeswax, both fresh from our family's farm. It doesn't get any more local than that!
item.excerpt:encoded: Cruise in style! One organic wooden toy car - our SUNDAY CRUISER - for your little one. You choose the color!

item.title: Brewing Mug
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded: Made in Japan of 20% post-consumer recycled ceramic, this ivory mug with the simple, classic design commemorates our inaugural year of brewing rich, flavorful coffee. The mug holds up to 14 fl oz and features an interior line that designates "Tall" size, for a perfectly-measured pour.
item.excerpt:encoded: A coffee mug made of 20% post-consumer recycled material that celebrates the inaugural year.

item.title: Chambord Coffee Press
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded: This classic 4-cup coffee press is still made with the same painstaking craftsmanship as the original from the fifties, but this latest version has a new chrome-plated steel frame and lid that will last for years. It features a wide, matte-black polypropylene handle that provides a cool, comfortable grip and adds to the modern style of the design. The borosilicate glass carafe is heat-resistant, and the entire press is dishwasher safe.
item.excerpt:encoded: The original coffee press with a new polished look. Brews up to 4 cups of rich, flavorful coffee.

item.title: 16oz Reserve Mug
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded: Made of new bone china, this grande size Reserve Mug holds a generous 16 fl oz of freshly brewed coffee or other favorite beverage for your sipping pleasure. Especially created to celebrate our Reserve coffees, it makes a great gift for any occasion.
item.excerpt:encoded: A grande coffee mug with perfect weight and balance – featuring our Reserve logo.

item.title: Custom Steel Tumbler
item.dc:creator: jbyers
item.content:encoded: Just twist off the clear outer layer and use the dry erase marker included to write messages or doodle on the stainless steel or the clear plastic liner inside. And while you're focused on your artwork, this double-walled, insulating tumbler with flip-top lid will help keep hot beverages hot and cold liquids cold. Holds 16 fl oz and fits standard car cup holders.
item.excerpt:encoded: A customizable stainless steel tumbler with marker for unleashing your creativity.
